Date and Time - Format Specifier
Date and time format specifier is a special character that enables you to display the data and time values in different formats.

Format specifier                                             Name

d—---------------------------------------------------    Short date
 D—--------------------------------------Long date
f—---------------------------------------full date/time(short time)
F—---------------------------------------’’’’’’’’’’’’’’’’’’’’’’’’’(long time)
g—--------------------------------------------General data/time(short time)
G—---------------------------------------’’’’’’’’’’’’’’’’’’’’’’’’’’’’’’’’’’’’’’’’’’’’’’’’(long time)
M or m —---------------------------------month day
t—------------------------------------short time
T—-------------------------------------long time
Y—-------------------------------------year


Eg:- y small y hai
Y-9
Yy-19
yyyy-2019


Eg:-
Main k andar-
    DateTime dt=DateTime.Now;
    Console.WriteLine("{0 :d}",dt);

o/p:-    12/04/2025

{0 :d}- format specifier hai to dt k andar date store ho gya h dt ne format specifier ko de diya h print karwane k liye
DateTime - predefined hai .net k andar


  DateTime dt=DateTime.Now;
    Console.WriteLine("{0 :D}",dt);
o/p-Thursday, 04 December 2025



Statement and Expression and Operators
Statement :-  statement is a single instruction that tells the computer to perform a specific action
Or
To perform the tasks , programmers provide instruction . these instructions are called statement.
Statement can contain expressions.
Eg- assign the value , loop , addition etc;

 Operator ➖
       int a=10;
      int b=30;
      bool c= a && b;
      Console.WriteLine(c); //error Operator '&&' cannot be applied to operands of type 'int' and 'int'

Ternary operator :- include a special type decision making operator ? : called ternary operator.


Login System :-
   Console.WriteLine("Enter your email");
    String email =Console.ReadLine();
    if(email == "baba@gmail.com"){
         Console.WriteLine("Enter your password");
         String password =Console.ReadLine();
         if(password == "123baba"){
                Console.WriteLine("Login done");
         }
    }
    else {
        Console.WriteLine("invalid");
    }
    
    }


Switch case ➖
Kab use karte h jab bhut sara if else statement ho jaye tab hum switch use kare ge
or
To avoid using multiple if statement 

Note :- break nhi likho ge error aa jaye ga har case k andar har case me break hona jaruri h    c#- error  and c,c++,java me no error

 int a=10;
    switch(a){
        case 10:
         Console.WriteLine("invalid");
         break;
          case 1:
         Console.WriteLine("invalid");
         break;
          case 2:
         Console.WriteLine("invalid");
        
         
    }   //  error- break nhi h


 int a=17;
    switch(a){
        case 10:
         Console.WriteLine("invalid");
         break;
          case 1:
         Console.WriteLine("invalid");
         break;
          case 2:
         Console.WriteLine("invalid");
        break;
        default:
          Console.WriteLine("iid");
          break;
        
         
    }

// default me bhi break lage ga
Case k andar condition nhi de sakte h 
Case age .=5;

  int a=17;
    switch(a){
        case 10:
        case 9:
        case 7:
         Console.WriteLine("invalid");
         break;
          case 1:
         Console.WriteLine("invalid");
         break;
          case 2:
         Console.WriteLine("invalid");
        break;
        default:
          Console.WriteLine("iid");
          break;
        
         
    }   // aise bhi likh sakte h bhut saare same case ek hi o/p de raha h to aise likh denge

